SIMPLE: scowl
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scowl
<hw>Scowl</hw> <pr>(skoul)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Scowled</conjf> <pr>(skould)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Scowling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Akin to Dan.
<ets>skule</ets>; cf. Icel. <ets>skolla</ets> to skulk, LG.
<ets>schulen</ets> to hide one's self, D. <ets>schuilen</ets>, G.
<ets>schielen</ets> to squint, Dan. <ets>skele</ets>, Sw.
<ets>skela</ets>, AS. <ets>sceolh</ets> squinting. Cf.
<er>Skulk</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To wrinkle the brows, as in
frowning or displeasure; to put on a frowning look; to look sour,
sullen, severe, or angry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She <qex>scowled</qex> and frowned with froward countenance.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, to look gloomy, dark, or threatening; to
lower.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>scowling</xex> heavens.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Thomson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scowl</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scowl
<hw>Scowl</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To look at or repel
with a scowl or a frown.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To express by a scowl; <as>as, to <ex>scowl</ex>
defiance</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scowl</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Scowl
<hw>Scowl</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The wrinkling of the
brows or face in frowing; the expression of displeasure, sullenness, or
discontent in the countenance; an angry frown.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With solemn phiz, and critic <qex>scowl</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Lloyd.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, gloom; dark or threatening aspect.</def>
<rj><au>Burns.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A ruddy storm, whose <qex>scowl</qex>⟦br⟧
Made heaven's radiant face look foul.</q>
<rj><qau>Crashaw.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scowlingly</ent>⟦br⟧
